%spark
def pca(train: Dataset[_], toAnalyze: Dataset[_]): Dataset[Tuple4[Double,Double,Double,Double]] = {
    new PCA().setInputCol("scaledFeatures").setOutputCol("pcaFeatures").setK(3).fit(train)
        .transform(toAnalyze)
        .map(r => (r.getAs[Vector]("pcaFeatures").toArray, r.getAs[Double]("manualLabel")))
        .map(t => (t._1.apply(0), t._1.apply(1), t._1.apply(2), t._2))
}

## PCA for complete dataset, with altered anomaly/normal ratio

msg.data: PCA for complete dataset, with altered anomaly/normal ratio

paragraphs.text:
%spark
val numPoints = 1000

//All by all
pca(data, data.filter($"manualLabel" === 0)).sample(true, numPoints.toDouble * 0.8 / data.filter($"manualLabel" === 0).count)
    .union(pca(data, data.filter($"manualLabel" > 0)).sample(true, numPoints.toDouble * 0.2 / data.filter($"manualLabel" > 0).count))
    .collect
    .sortBy(_._4)
    .foreach(x => println("%01.10f,%11.10f,%21.10f,%31.0f".format(x._1, x._2, x._3, x._4)))
